articles.title: Australia cuts interest rates to more than 2-year lows, downgrades economic growth forecast - CNBC
articles.description: The country's benchmark rates are now at to 3.6%, their lowest since April 2023
articles.content:
Australia's central bank cut its benchmark lending rates by 25 basis points on Tuesday, while downgrading the annual economic outlook for the country.
